American singer Christopher Maurice Brown better known as Chris Brown has released the music video to “Heat” featuring rapper, Gunna. Heat is off Chris Brown’s ninth studio album, Indigo. In the video, Brown mans a female clothing store with Gunna. The store is surrounded by lots of women who troop in later as soon as the store opens. A while later, Gunna is seen getting freaky with his sexy co-star in the dressing room, while Breezy doubles his pleasure with two women. The double-disc album features appearances by H.E.R., Lil’ Jon, Juvenile, Juicy J, Tyga, Joyner Lucas, Lil Wayne, Drake, Justin Bieber, Tory Lanez, Trey Songz, and Tank. Indigo debuted at number one on the US Billboard 200 with 108,000 album-equivalent units, which included 28,000 pure album sales in its first week, making it his third number-one album in the country. Watch “Heat” below:  